Introduction:

This is a black silk LORA that can improve the texture of the black silk in the picture.

Thickness: 8D

Color: black

Type: Glossy thigh-high over-the-knee socks

Don't be fooled by the small size of this LORA!

The features of this LORA are as follows:

  1. Made meticulously using differential extraction, so it is very small in size. Apart from affecting the texture of the stockings, it has a minor impact on other content in the picture.

  2. All made with high-definition camera shots of real people to ensure realistic effects.

  3. Because it has little effect on other content in the picture, it's okay even if the weight is set high.

Why make another one when there are already so many black silk LORAs? Because I found:

  1. Existing LORAs will pollute the picture to some extent. Either it's the clothes, or it's the shoes. Can we make a LORA that only affects the texture of the black silk and does not affect other content in the picture?

  2. Existing LORAs do not distinguish the thickness and style of stockings, so the overall state is somewhat chaotic.

So I made this LORA and will make a series of different thicknesses and textures of LORAs in the future. All are made from real-shot materials and made using differential extraction to ensure quality.

So this might be the best hi-silk LORA you've ever used.

Special note! The weight of this LORA should be between 0.5 and 1.5 for better effects, the weight needs to be set rather high!

You can find all the models at GOD-OF-GREED, GOD-OF-ENVY, GOD-OF-LOVE, GOD-OF-ANIME, GOD-OF-LUST, GOD-OF-JUSTICE, GOD-OF-TIME, GOD-OF-FANTASY, GOD-OF-JOY, GOD-OF-HORROR, GOD-OF-PRIDE, GOD-OF-PUNK, GOD-OF-STORMS, GOD-OF-EUPHORIA, GOD-OF-GLUTTONY, GOD-OF-THE-WEST, GOD-OF-BEAUTY, GOD-OF-SEDUCTION, and GOD-OF-PEACE.

This model is a mix of a few of my GOD series models, my FoolKat_Envy_2D-Blend_V1, DarkToon, Comi-Noir2 Sephia, and AnotherDamnArtModel. I also added a few lora files at low strength that add cyberpunk and steampunk elements to the model.

The model has Blessed2 VAE baked into it, so no VAE required.

All of the images I upload for this model are unedited and don't use any special extensions like ControlNet. I do not do any inpainting or img2img to correct errors. Why? Because you deserve to see how the model works without any touchup or special extensions like ControlNet. You can surely get better images by putting in the extra work, which I do for my personal images. The samples are just meant to showcase what the model can do raw with nothing but prompt engineering.

items.name: HD Helper
items.description:
High Definition without high res fix. Generate images 1024x1024 or greater directly. No upscaling or special highres fixes needed.


This is an experiment I have been working on that frankly turned out way better than I expected. Attach it to a model and it allows you to generate images much larger than you normally would be able to, directly. No more double heads, huge foreheads or multi layered scenes when going over 768 px.

This initial release will be improved upon. It was trained at 1024 px at various aspect ratios to expand the knowledge of the model out to there. I should be able to take it out quite a bit farther in the next versions. It is created with a training trick I have been experimenting with to rescale the contextual awareness of a model without changing its knowledge.

items.name: Neoki Ohae Style [Furry Eared Girls Edition]
items.description:
A somewhat "dreamy" style good at making cute cat girls. Or sheep girls. Or dog girls. Or any type of animal eared girl really. Plus frills, lots of frills, dresses and fluffy stuff.

How to use
Prompt normally, even just "1girl" works. Tags to try are "chibi" and various cat girls tags like "animal ear fluff", "cat ears", "tail" etc. Usually you only need "animal ear fluff".
Another tag to try is "simple background" in negatives, all the images in the dataset are generally very detailed. For more prompting tips see the sample images or the uploaded zip with training tags.

MISC
Trained on NAI with a dataset of 25 images at 512 resolution.
All sample images are raw txt2img upscales, no inpainting or helper embeddings used.
The training was done on a small subset of the artists images, as such the output of this LoRA is not an accurate representation neither in quality or style of the source material. Go support the artist >neoki ohaE< if you want the good stuff.
Standard LoRA version can be found >here<.

items.name: Humphrey Bogart Lora
items.description:
The stuff loras are made of...

Be nice, have fun!

Humphrey DeForest Bogart (/ËboÊÉ¡ÉËrt/;[1] December 25, 1899 â January 14, 1957), colloquially nicknamed Bogie, was an American film and stage actor. His performances in classic Hollywood cinema films made him an American cultural icon.[2] In 1999, the American Film Institute selected Bogart as the greatest male star of classic American cinema.[3]

Bogart began acting in Broadway shows,[4] beginning his career in motion pictures with Up the River (1930) for 20th Century Fox, and appeared in supporting roles for the next decade, regularly portraying gangsters. He was praised for his work as Duke Mantee in The Petrified Forest (1936), but remained cast secondary to other actors at Warner Bros. who received leading roles. Bogart also received positive reviews for his performance as gangster Hugh "Baby Face" Martin, in Dead End (1937), directed by William Wyler.

His breakthrough from supporting roles to stardom was set in motion with High Sierra (1941) and catapulted in The Maltese Falcon (1941), considered one of the first great noir films.[5] Bogart's private detectives, Sam Spade (in The Maltese Falcon) and Philip Marlowe (in 1946's The Big Sleep), became the models for detectives in other noir films. His most significant romantic lead role was with Ingrid Bergman in Casablanca (1942), which earned him his first nomination for the Academy Award for Best Actor. 44-year-old Bogart and 19-year-old Lauren Bacall fell in love during filming of To Have and Have Not (1944). In 1945, a few months after principal photography for The Big Sleep, their second film together, he divorced his third wife and married Bacall. After their marriage, they played each other's love interest in the mystery thrillers Dark Passage (1947) and Key Largo (1948). Raymond Chandler, in a 1946 letter, wrote that "Like Edward G. Robinson when he was younger, all he has to do to dominate a scene is to enter it."[6]

Bogart's performances in The Treasure of the Sierra Madre (1948) and In a Lonely Place (1950) are now considered among his best, although they were not recognized as such when the films were released.[7] He reprised those unsettled, unstable characters as a World War II naval-vessel commander in The Caine Mutiny (1954), which was a critical and commercial hit and earned him another Best Actor nomination. He won the Academy Award for Best Actor for his portrayal of a cantankerous river steam launch skipper opposite Katharine Hepburn's missionary in the World War I African adventure The African Queen (1951). Other significant roles in his later years included The Barefoot Contessa (1954) with Ava Gardner and his on-screen competition with William Holden for Audrey Hepburn in Sabrina (1954). A heavy smoker and drinker, Bogart died from esophageal cancer in January 1957. Lauren Bacall said of him, "There was something that made him able to be a man of his own and it showed through his work. There was also a purity, which is amazing considering the parts he played. Something solid too. I think as time goes by we all believe less and less. Here was someone who believed in something."[8]

items.name: Pockey | Plush Boys
items.description:
Here's "Pockey", a LoCon trained on my art style. Since I generally draw thick men, it is basically a thick man LoCon!

Works at weight 1, but you could lower it to get different effects. Trigger word is pockey (because "pocket" and "cosmic" caused too much infection from the tokens.)

My dataset consisted of 98 of my drawings cropped to 512x512. I used the default settings suggested by the HollowStrawberry Lora Trainer based on the dataset size: 3 repeats, 10 epochs, batch size 2, unet learinng rate 5e-4, text encoder learning rate 1e-4, learning rate scheduler cosine with restarts with 3 restarts, 5% warmup ratio, network dim 16, network alpha 8, conv dim 8, conv alpha 1.

The example images had no inpainting or controlnet, to show you what you would get right out of the box. The style is somewhat influenced by the model, so different models will give different effects. It is very responsive to body shape and skin color tags. "obliques" is great to use. It has a tendency toward open mouths, which I will work on in the next revision.

items.name: Realistic Dark Skin - Concept LORA
items.description:
Problem : When you add "dark skin", using prompts, realistic checkpoints very often generate African facial features and curly hair.

This lora is a try to add darker skin tones without modifying facial features and hair style very much.

I made grid to compare my lora, SSAHC and 0 lora.

Trained on SDv1-5-pruned with 58 pictures.
Best result with weight between : 0.3-1.
Clip skip = 1

Prompt activator : dark skin, ebony, latina

You will need to play with weight like (ebony:0.3) to only get darker skin and don't swap ethnicity. Latina prompt is very light skin.

I do not support any indecent images generated of all persons in this model, I do not support selling generated images of persons in this model. please refrain from what they have been posting online.

All persons in this model are 21+ and not a minor, please DO NOT post explicit nudity, suggestive content, or pornographic content online using this model. Refer to CivitAi TOS for more details.

===

Request or Suggestion Rule:

  1. No request for a minor!

  2. The requested should have public data (not private)

  3. Should have more than 30 good-quality images

  4. Since all requests or suggestions are free, I will still need to like your request, otherwise its a work not a hobby for me.

  5. Be a decent human being and leave a review if your request is up It takes you only 5 mins while it takes me hours, electricity, and effort to do your requests.

  6. If you don't get what you want, do not review the bomb, there could be other creators' models or Lora that can get better results than mine, use theirs instead, and leave a good review on them too, support any other creators for their hard works!

NOTE: I will keep updating more actresses in versions update

===

Usage Guide

--

A. Lora Weight

  • 0.1 ~ 0.4 -- is to combine multiple faces or features, or if you experience overbaking

  • 0.5 ~ 0.7 -- is a balanced weight to get still accurate features but with more flexibility

  • 0.8 ~ 1.0 -- is to create an accurate representation of the features.

B. CFG Scale

  • A lower CFG Scale means AI gets more creative and less overbaking problems.

  • A higher CFG Scale means results get very accurate with training sets and are more prone to overbaking problems.

  • Dynamic CFG Threshold, using this method allows you to bump up quality and achieve photorealistic easily, but with lycoris, I found out recently that this method actually lowers the success rate, so only use it when you are composing with a Lora / model that works fine with this method.

C. Sampling Steps, High Res Fix & Upscaling

  • I like to use sampling steps at 50, with high res steps at 20, or 1/2 of the sampling steps.

  • I find that 2M Karras works better and faster than SDE Karras. with ERSGAN 4x+ method + ERSGAN 4x for Upscaling. This method actually gives quite good results without being too sharp or too plasticky

  • Upscaling - GPFGAN @0.25, Codeformer @0.3 & Codeformer Weight @0.15 seems to yield superior results.

Enjoy.
